{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"\"Pheromone\" is a very powerful word."},{"time":4318,"text":"It conjures up sex, abandon, loss of control,"},{"time":8462,"text":"and you can see, it's very important as a word."},{"time":12154,"text":"But it's only 50 years old. It was invented in 1959."},{"time":17437,"text":"Now, if you put that word into the web,"},{"time":19986,"text":"as you may have done,"},{"time":21496,"text":"you'll come up with millions of hits,"},{"time":23888,"text":"and almost all of those sites are trying to sell you"},{"time":26533,"text":"something to make you irresistible"},{"time":28792,"text":"for 10 dollars or more."},{"time":31865,"text":"Now, this is a very attractive idea,"},{"time":34088,"text":"and the molecules they mention"},{"time":36530,"text":"sound really science-y."},{"time":38444,"text":"They've got lots of syllables."},{"time":40028,"text":"It's things like androstenol, androstenone"},{"time":42901,"text":"or androstadienone."},{"time":45342,"text":"It gets better and better,"},{"time":46984,"text":"and when you combine that with white lab coats,"},{"time":49774,"text":"you must imagine that there is"},{"time":51186,"text":"fantastic science behind this."},{"time":53700,"text":"But sadly, these are fraudulent claims"},{"time":58822,"text":"supported by dodgy science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62161,"text":"The problem is that, although there are many"},{"time":64779,"text":"good scientists working on what they think"},{"time":67324,"text":"are human pheromones,"},{"time":69194,"text":"and they're publishing in respectable journals,"},{"time":71799,"text":"at the basis of this,"},{"time":73380,"text":"despite very sophisticated experiments,"},{"time":76716,"text":"there really is no good science behind it,"},{"time":79269,"text":"because it's based on a problem,"},{"time":82561,"text":"which is nobody has systematically gone through"},{"time":86011,"text":"all the odors that humans produce --"},{"time":88112,"text":"and there are thousands of\nmolecules that we give off."},{"time":90890,"text":"We're mammals. We produce a lot of smell."},{"time":94000,"text":"Nobody has gone through systematically"},{"time":96144,"text":"to work out which molecules really are pheromones."},{"time":98911,"text":"They've just plucked a few,"},{"time":100541,"text":"and all these experiments are based on those,"},{"time":102430,"text":"but there's no good evidence at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105440,"text":"Now, that's not to say"},{"time":107618,"text":"that smell is not important to people."},{"time":109780,"text":"It is, and some people are real enthusiasts,"},{"time":113282,"text":"and one of these was Napoleon."},{"time":116779,"text":"And famously, you may remember"},{"time":118571,"text":"that out on the campaign trail for war,"},{"time":121668,"text":"he wrote to his lover, Empress Josephine,"},{"time":124475,"text":"saying, \"Don't wash. I'm coming home.\""},{"time":127709,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":128311,"text":"So he didn't want to lose any of her richness"},{"time":131232,"text":"in the days before he'd get home,"},{"time":133581,"text":"and it is still, you'll find websites"},{"time":135958,"text":"that offer this as a major quirk."},{"time":139860,"text":"At the same time, though,"},{"time":141024,"text":"we spend about as much money"},{"time":143477,"text":"taking the smells off us"},{"time":145248,"text":"as putting them back on in perfumes,"},{"time":147969,"text":"and perfumes are a multi-billion-dollar business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152160,"text":"So what I want to do in the rest of this talk"},{"time":154563,"text":"is tell you about what pheromones really are,"},{"time":159841,"text":"tell you why I think we would expect"},{"time":162839,"text":"humans to have pheromones,"},{"time":165587,"text":"tell you about some of the\nconfusions in pheromones,"},{"time":170080,"text":"and then finally, I want to end with"},{"time":172872,"text":"a promising avenue which shows us"},{"time":174842,"text":"the way we ought to be going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178990,"text":"So the ancient Greeks knew"},{"time":183171,"text":"that dogs sent invisible signals between each other."},{"time":187225,"text":"A female dog in heat"},{"time":189599,"text":"sent an invisible signal to male dogs"},{"time":191515,"text":"for miles around,"},{"time":192970,"text":"and it wasn't a sound, it was a smell."},{"time":195075,"text":"You could take the smell from the female dog,"},{"time":197256,"text":"and the dogs would chase the cloth."},{"time":199719,"text":"But the problem for everybody"},{"time":201327,"text":"who could see this effect"},{"time":203440,"text":"was that you couldn't identify the molecules."},{"time":205062,"text":"You couldn't demonstrate it was chemical."},{"time":207515,"text":"The reason for that, of course,"},{"time":208830,"text":"is that each of these animals"},{"time":210245,"text":"produces tiny quantities,"},{"time":211851,"text":"and in the case of the dog,"},{"time":213510,"text":"males dogs can smell it, but we can't smell it."},{"time":216412,"text":"And it was only in 1959 that a German team,"},{"time":220770,"text":"after spending 20 years in\nsearch of these molecules,"},{"time":224122,"text":"discovered, identified, the first pheromone,"},{"time":227903,"text":"and this was the sex pheromone of a silk moth."},{"time":231181,"text":"Now, this was an inspired choice \nby Adolf Butenandt and his team,"},{"time":234855,"text":"because he needed half a million moths"},{"time":236981,"text":"to get enough material to do the chemical analysis."},{"time":240008,"text":"But he created the model"},{"time":242097,"text":"for how you should go about pheromone analysis."},{"time":244461,"text":"He basically went through systematically,"},{"time":247142,"text":"showing that only the molecule in question"},{"time":250087,"text":"was the one that stimulated the males,"},{"time":251953,"text":"not all the others."},{"time":254006,"text":"He analyzed it very carefully."},{"time":256164,"text":"He synthesized the molecule,"},{"time":257981,"text":"and then tried the synthesized\nmolecule on the males"},{"time":261289,"text":"and got them to respond and showed it was,"},{"time":264150,"text":"indeed, that molecule."},{"time":265910,"text":"That's closing the circle."},{"time":268060,"text":"That's the thing which has\nnever been done with humans:"},{"time":270765,"text":"nothing systematic, no real demonstration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274375,"text":"With that new concept,"},{"time":276109,"text":"we needed a new word,"},{"time":277818,"text":"and that was the word \"pheromone,\""},{"time":280653,"text":"and it's basically transferred excitement,"},{"time":284254,"text":"transferred between individuals,"},{"time":286523,"text":"and since 1959, pheromones have been found"},{"time":289349,"text":"right the way across the animal kingdom,"},{"time":291224,"text":"in male animals, in female animals."},{"time":293426,"text":"It works just as well underwater"},{"time":294971,"text":"for goldfish and lobsters."},{"time":296993,"text":"And almost every mammal you can think of"},{"time":298740,"text":"has had a pheromone identified,"},{"time":300563,"text":"and of course, an enormous number of insects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304393,"text":"So we know that pheromones exist"},{"time":306362,"text":"right the way across the animal kingdom."},{"time":309423,"text":"What about humans?"},{"time":311196,"text":"Well, the first thing, of course,"},{"time":312444,"text":"is that we're mammals,"},{"time":314101,"text":"and mammals are smelly."},{"time":315660,"text":"As any dog owner can tell you,"},{"time":317536,"text":"we smell, they smell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319517,"text":"But the real reason we might think"},{"time":321498,"text":"that humans have pheromones"},{"time":323323,"text":"is the change that occurs as we grow up."},{"time":326541,"text":"The smell of a room of teenagers"},{"time":328992,"text":"is quite different"},{"time":330481,"text":"from the smell of a room of small children."},{"time":333301,"text":"What's changed? And of course, it's puberty."},{"time":336173,"text":"Along with the pubic hair"},{"time":337632,"text":"and the hair in the armpits,"},{"time":339325,"text":"new glands start to secrete in those places,"},{"time":343067,"text":"and that's what's making the change in smell."},{"time":345682,"text":"If we were any other kind of mammal,"},{"time":347830,"text":"or any other kind of animal,"},{"time":349019,"text":"we would say,"},{"time":350156,"text":"\"That must be something to do with pheromones,\""},{"time":352028,"text":"and we'd start looking properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354684,"text":"But there are some problems, and this is why,"},{"time":356660,"text":"I think, people have not looked for"},{"time":359729,"text":"pheromones so effectively in humans."},{"time":362646,"text":"There are, indeed, problems."},{"time":364217,"text":"And the first of these"},{"time":366401,"text":"is perhaps surprising."},{"time":367918,"text":"It's all about culture."},{"time":369752,"text":"Now moths don't learn a lot"},{"time":371899,"text":"about what is good to smell, but humans do,"},{"time":375516,"text":"and up to the age of about four,"},{"time":377362,"text":"any smell, no matter how rancid,"},{"time":380081,"text":"is simply interesting."},{"time":381880,"text":"And I understand that the major role of parents"},{"time":383932,"text":"is to stop kids putting their fingers in poo,"},{"time":387613,"text":"because it's always something nice to smell."},{"time":390411,"text":"But gradually we learn what's not good,"},{"time":393102,"text":"and one of the things we learn"},{"time":394592,"text":"at the same time as what is not good"},{"time":396727,"text":"is what is good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398485,"text":"Now, the cheese behind me"},{"time":400747,"text":"is a British, if not an English, delicacy."},{"time":404698,"text":"It's ripe blue Stilton."},{"time":408135,"text":"Liking it is incomprehensible to\npeople from other countries."},{"time":412497,"text":"Every culture has its own special food"},{"time":415782,"text":"and national delicacy."},{"time":417878,"text":"If you were to come from Iceland,"},{"time":419930,"text":"your national dish"},{"time":421254,"text":"is deep rotted shark."},{"time":424230,"text":"Now, all of these things are acquired tastes,"},{"time":426360,"text":"but they form almost a badge of identity."},{"time":429520,"text":"You're part of the in-group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434340,"text":"The second thing is the sense of smell."},{"time":437922,"text":"Each of us has a unique odor world,"},{"time":441391,"text":"in the sense that what we smell,"},{"time":443930,"text":"we each smell a completely different world."},{"time":446789,"text":"Now, smell was the hardest"},{"time":448498,"text":"of the senses to crack,"},{"time":450359,"text":"and the Nobel Prize awarded to"},{"time":452074,"text":"Richard Axel and Linda Buck"},{"time":453707,"text":"was only awarded in 2004"},{"time":456140,"text":"for their discovery of how smell works."},{"time":458930,"text":"It's really hard,"},{"time":460307,"text":"but in essence, nerves from the brain"},{"time":462898,"text":"go up into the nose"},{"time":465111,"text":"and on these nerves exposed in the nose"},{"time":467492,"text":"to the outside air are receptors,"},{"time":470546,"text":"and odor molecules coming in on a sniff"},{"time":473695,"text":"interact with these receptors,"},{"time":475845,"text":"and if they bond, they send the nerve a signal"},{"time":480104,"text":"which goes back into the brain."},{"time":482412,"text":"We don't just have one kind of receptor."},{"time":484474,"text":"If you're a human, you have about 400"},{"time":486350,"text":"different kinds of receptors,"},{"time":488415,"text":"and the brain knows what you're smelling"},{"time":491382,"text":"because of the combination of receptors"},{"time":493193,"text":"and nerve cells that they trigger,"},{"time":495706,"text":"sending messages up to the brain"},{"time":497264,"text":"in a combinatorial fashion."},{"time":500170,"text":"But it's a bit more complicated,"},{"time":501160,"text":"because each of those 400"},{"time":503295,"text":"comes in various variants,"},{"time":505446,"text":"and depending which variant you have,"},{"time":507517,"text":"you might smell coriander, or cilantro, that herb,"},{"time":511699,"text":"either as something delicious and savory"},{"time":514317,"text":"or something like soap."},{"time":516491,"text":"So we each have an individual world of smell,"},{"time":519177,"text":"and that complicates anything"},{"time":520818,"text":"when we're studying smell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523114,"text":"Well, we really ought to talk about armpits,"},{"time":525806,"text":"and I have to say that I do\nhave particularly good ones."},{"time":529202,"text":"Now, I'm not going to share them with you,"},{"time":531204,"text":"but this is the place that most people"},{"time":533183,"text":"have looked for pheromones."},{"time":534920,"text":"There is one good reason,"},{"time":536423,"text":"which is, the great apes have armpits"},{"time":539827,"text":"as their unique characteristic."},{"time":542155,"text":"The other primates have scent glands"},{"time":544556,"text":"in other parts of the body."},{"time":546386,"text":"The great apes have these armpits"},{"time":548740,"text":"full of secretory glands"},{"time":550957,"text":"producing smells all the time,"},{"time":553298,"text":"enormous numbers of molecules."},{"time":556998,"text":"When they're secreted from the glands,"},{"time":558701,"text":"the molecules are odorless."},{"time":560705,"text":"They have no smell at all,"},{"time":562780,"text":"and it's only the wonderful bacteria"},{"time":564749,"text":"growing on the rainforest of hair"},{"time":566962,"text":"that actually produces the smells"},{"time":568418,"text":"that we know and love."},{"time":570439,"text":"And so incidentally, if you want to reduce"},{"time":572339,"text":"the amount of smell,"},{"time":573769,"text":"clear-cutting your armpits"},{"time":575689,"text":"is a very effective way of reducing"},{"time":577945,"text":"the habitat for bacteria,"},{"time":579459,"text":"and you'll find they remain less smelly"},{"time":581796,"text":"for much longer."},{"time":583890,"text":"But although we've focused on armpits,"},{"time":586436,"text":"I think it's partly because they're the least"},{"time":587803,"text":"embarrassing place to go and ask people for samples."},{"time":591770,"text":"There is actually another reason why we might not"},{"time":594382,"text":"be looking for a universal sex pheromone there,"},{"time":597158,"text":"and that's because 20 percent\nof the world's population"},{"time":600997,"text":"doesn't have smelly armpits like me."},{"time":604442,"text":"And these are people from China, Japan,"},{"time":608358,"text":"Korea, and other parts of northeast Asia."},{"time":610953,"text":"They simply don't secrete those odorless precursors"},{"time":614477,"text":"that the bacteria love to use to produce the smells"},{"time":618730,"text":"that in an ethnocentric way we always thought of"},{"time":621079,"text":"as characteristic of armpits."},{"time":623184,"text":"So it doesn't apply to 20 percent of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627691,"text":"So what should we be doing"},{"time":630693,"text":"in our search for human pheromones?"},{"time":633746,"text":"I'm fairly convinced that we do have them."},{"time":636198,"text":"We're mammals, like everybody else"},{"time":638151,"text":"who's a mammal, and we probably do have them."},{"time":642130,"text":"But what I think we should do"},{"time":643713,"text":"is go right back to the beginning,"},{"time":645652,"text":"and basically look all over the body."},{"time":647991,"text":"No matter how embarrassing,"},{"time":649682,"text":"we need to search and go for the first time"},{"time":653060,"text":"where no one else has dared tread."},{"time":655520,"text":"It's going to be difficult,"},{"time":656668,"text":"it's going to be embarrassing, but we need to look."},{"time":659243,"text":"We also need to go back to the ideas"},{"time":662190,"text":"that Butenandt used when he\nwas studying the silk moth."},{"time":665457,"text":"We need to go back and look systematically"},{"time":668925,"text":"at all the molecules that are being produced,"},{"time":671063,"text":"and work out which ones are really involved."},{"time":673496,"text":"It isn't good enough simply to pluck a couple"},{"time":675602,"text":"and say, \"They'll do.\""},{"time":677546,"text":"We have to actually demonstrate"},{"time":678945,"text":"that they really have the effects we claim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681755,"text":"There is one team that I'm\nactually very impressed by."},{"time":684989,"text":"They're in France, and their previous success"},{"time":688165,"text":"was identifying the rabbit mammary pheromone."},{"time":692542,"text":"They've turned their attention now"},{"time":695111,"text":"to human babies and mothers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698296,"text":"So this is a baby having a drink of milk"},{"time":701367,"text":"from its mother's breast."},{"time":704010,"text":"Her nipple is completely hidden"},{"time":706193,"text":"by the baby's head,"},{"time":707439,"text":"but what you'll notice is a white droplet"},{"time":711190,"text":"with an arrow pointing to it,"},{"time":712971,"text":"and that's the secretion from the areolar glands."},{"time":716170,"text":"Now, we all have them, men and women,"},{"time":719160,"text":"and these are the little bumps around the nipple,"},{"time":721978,"text":"and if you're a lactating woman,"},{"time":723937,"text":"these start to secrete."},{"time":726274,"text":"It's a very interesting secretion."},{"time":728863,"text":"What Benoist Schaal and his team developed"},{"time":731866,"text":"was a simple test to investigate"},{"time":734273,"text":"what the effect of this secretion might be,"},{"time":737079,"text":"in effect, a simple bioassay."},{"time":740055,"text":"So this is a sleeping baby,"},{"time":742730,"text":"and under its nose, we've put a clean glass rod."},{"time":747719,"text":"The baby remains sleeping,"},{"time":749830,"text":"showing no interest at all."},{"time":752171,"text":"But if we go to any mother"},{"time":754245,"text":"who is secreting from the areolar glands,"},{"time":756674,"text":"so it's not about recognition,"},{"time":758251,"text":"it can be from any mother,"},{"time":760479,"text":"if we take the secretion"},{"time":761831,"text":"and now put it under the baby's nose,"},{"time":764735,"text":"we get a very different reaction."},{"time":766826,"text":"It's a connoisseur's reaction of delight,"},{"time":769810,"text":"and it opens its mouth"},{"time":771870,"text":"and sticks out its tongue"},{"time":773523,"text":"and starts to suck."},{"time":775610,"text":"Now, since this is from any mother,"},{"time":777950,"text":"it could really be a pheromone."},{"time":779742,"text":"It's not about individual recognition."},{"time":781521,"text":"Any mother will do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783397,"text":"Now, why is this important,"},{"time":784860,"text":"apart from being simply very interesting?"},{"time":787318,"text":"It's because women vary"},{"time":789125,"text":"in the number of areolar glands that they have,"},{"time":791898,"text":"and there is a correlation between the ease"},{"time":794094,"text":"with which babies start to suckle"},{"time":796636,"text":"and the number of areolar glands she has."},{"time":798498,"text":"It appears that the more secretions she's got,"},{"time":801296,"text":"the more likely the baby is to suckle quickly."},{"time":804958,"text":"If you're a mammal,"},{"time":806418,"text":"the most dangerous time in life"},{"time":808961,"text":"is the first few hours after birth."},{"time":811270,"text":"You have to get that first drink of milk,"},{"time":815030,"text":"and if you don't get it, you won't survive."},{"time":818521,"text":"You'll be dead."},{"time":819985,"text":"Since many babies actually find it difficult"},{"time":822623,"text":"to take that first meal,"},{"time":824272,"text":"because they're not getting the right stimulus,"},{"time":826249,"text":"if we could identify what that molecule was,"},{"time":829459,"text":"and the French team are being very cautious,"},{"time":831446,"text":"but if we could identify the molecule,"},{"time":833561,"text":"synthesize it, it would then mean"},{"time":836355,"text":"premature babies would be more likely to suckle,"},{"time":838261,"text":"and every baby would have a better chance"},{"time":841189,"text":"of survival."},{"time":842510,"text":"So what I want to argue is this is one example"},{"time":845050,"text":"of where a systematic, really scientific approach"},{"time":848646,"text":"can actually bring you a real understanding"},{"time":851368,"text":"of pheromones."},{"time":852476,"text":"There could be all sorts of medical interventions."},{"time":855090,"text":"There could be all sorts of things"},{"time":856344,"text":"that humans are doing with pheromones"},{"time":858044,"text":"that we simply don't know at the moment."},{"time":860092,"text":"What we need to remember is pheromones"},{"time":861978,"text":"are not just about sex."},{"time":863356,"text":"They're about all sorts of things to do"},{"time":865072,"text":"with a mammal's life."},{"time":866795,"text":"So do go forward and do search for more."},{"time":869484,"text":"There's lots to find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870524,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872390,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}